Product description

Shop from a wide range of T-Shirt from CHKOKKO. Perfect for your everyday use, you could pair it with a stylish pair of Jeans or Trousers complete the look.

From the manufacturer

Chkokko Turtle Neck Men's Tshirt

Chkokko brings to you this turtle neck t-shirt which is made from cotton and polyester and is available in attractive colours. This t-shirt has been designed keeping in mind the latest trends in contemporary casual fashion. The t-shirt combines style with the fashion of today and makes you stand out among others when you adorn it.

Read more

Fabric

Made from cotton and polyester with a ratio of 52% and 48%, the t-shirt is comfortable to wear during high temperatures to beat the heat. Cotton is a fabric which is light on the skin and is a suitable fabric for outfits when the sun is up and high.

Read more

Style Tip

Pair this t-shirt with a pair of stylish jeans, pants or chinos for a complete casual look for a casual event, a party or an evening with friends.

Read more

How are ratings calculated?
To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

5.0 out of 5 stars The BEST Turtle Neck T-Shirt You Can Find on Amazon.in
Reviewed in India on 20 April 2019
Size: SColour: Bottle GreenVerified Purchase
I purchased the black variant of the shirt a few weeks ago and was impressed with the quality of the brand. I also bought a few other turtle neck t-shirts of other brands. But non were as good as this brand. They had either loose neck or they were of thin material which were overpriced. I later ordered 5 more of different colour shades of CHKOKKO brand. All of them were of same quality which are good. The material is thick and will absorb sweat easily and will keep you warm during cold times.
A few thing they could have improved according to me are, the black and the navy blue shirts are almost identical. One could easily mistake blue for black. Similar is the case of maroon and magenta varieties. One is a little lighter than the other but otherwise similar.
They could have made more colour options, like white, ivory, sky blue, red etc.
